ont-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">[21]</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><a name="_Ref364783306"><span style="color:#365f91; font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">Bagdanavici</span><span style="color:#365f91; font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">us, A.; Jenkins, N. (2013). “Exergy and Exergoeconomic analysis of a Compressed Air Energy Storage combined with a District Energy System.” Energy Conversion and Management (under review)</span></a><span style="color:#365f91; font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">.</span></p><p style="line-height:15pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="color:#365f91; font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:15pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="color:#365f91; font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">September 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:8pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:8pt">190g/kWh (carbon content of natural gas) ÷ 90% (boiler efficiency)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn2"></a><a href="#_ftnref2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:8pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:8pt">190gkWh ÷ 55% (CCGT efficiency) ÷ 93% (transmission </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:8pt">&amp;</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:8pt"> distribution efficiency) ÷ 300% (heat pump efficiency)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn3"></a><a href="#_ftnref3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:8pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:8pt">190gkWh ÷ 55% (CCGT efficiency) ÷ 85% (heat ne</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:8pt">twork efficiency) ÷ 700% (thermal</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:8pt"> generation Z factor or virtual heat pump efficiency)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn4"></a><a href="#_ftnref4">[4]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:8pt"> </span><a href="http://www.energysavingtrust.org.uk/About-us/The-Foundation/At-Home-with-Water"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Verdana; font-size:8pt; text-decoration:underline">www.energysavingtrust.org.uk/About-us/The-Foundation/At-Home-with-Water</span></a><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:8pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn5"></a><a href="#_ftnref5">[5]</a><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:8pt"> </span><a href="http://www.ons.gov.uk/ons/rel/regional-trends/area-based-analysis/household-energy-consumption-in-england-and-wales--2005-11/art-household-energy-consumption-in-england-and-wales--2005-11.html"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Verdana; font-size:8pt; text-decoration:underline">www.ons.gov.uk/ons/rel/regional-trends/area-based-analysis/household-energy-consumption-in-england-and-wales--2005-11/art-household-energy-consu</span><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Verdana; font-size:8pt; text-decoration:underline">mption-in-england-and-wales--2005-11.html</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn6"></a><a href="#_ftnref6">[6]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:8pt"> </span><a href="http://www.ukerc.ac.uk/support/tiki-index.php?page=RF3LEnergyEfficientHomeRenovations"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Verdana; font-size:8pt; text-decoration:underline">www.ukerc.ac.uk/support/tiki-index.php?page=RF3LEnergyEfficientHomeRenovations</span></a><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:8pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn7"></a><a href="#_ftnref7">[7]</a><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:8pt"> </sp